Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 27.56 Points
NEW DELHI , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- The sensitive index on the Bombay Stock Exchange ( BSE ) market Monday closed at 2,810.66 as against the last close of 2 , 783.10 , netting a gain of 27.56 points .
The national index improved by 11.77 points to 1,254.10 from the previous close of 1 , 242.33 .
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were quoted marginally up at 291.54 and 113.86 compared with the previous close of 289.03 and 113.17 respectively .
Equities recovered its initial losses and even posted smart gains , lifting the sensitive index by over 27 points on the stock market Monday following late purchases by foreign funds and financial institutions leading to short covering by operators .
